arm64: dts: rockchip: m28k: fix gmac1 MAC address

RK3528 has no fused MAC and the m28k gmac DTS provides none, so the kernel
assigns a random locally-administered MAC each boot -> DHCP IP keeps moving.
Pin a stable locally-administered MAC. Single-board value; change per unit
or switch to nvmem/cpuid derivation if deploying multiple boards.

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-mangopi-m28.dtsi	2026-06-13 11:44:42.880113481 +0800
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3528-mangopi-m28.dtsi	2026-06-13 11:44:42.881985204 +0800
@@ -152,6 +152,7 @@
 
 &gmac1 {
 	clock_in_out = "output";
+	local-mac-address = [02 00 28 6b 00 01];
 	phy-handle = <&rgmii_phy>;
 	phy-mode = "rgmii-id";
 	phy-supply = <&vcc_3v3>;
